review_blob: Very fizzy, hard to discern flavor.  Eventually toffee reveals itself.  Nice brown appearance, but also flat looking. Burnt chocolate aroma.  Bitter finish.
Strong ruby color but also a bit flat in appearance. Sweet, burnt caramel with perfume aroma.  Full and creamy on the palate with a bitter finish.
beer_name: Bear Republic Hop Rod Rye Ale

review_blob: Full, fun, foamy white head first out of the bottle.  Smooth, authentically sincere.  Citrus and straw overtones, but then bitter.  Beautiful looking with lively but not fizzy carbonation.
